window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Do you want a proven way to reduce your ADHD symptoms in just a few minutes? Keep reading....</b></p> <p>Meditation is one of the most popular forms of complimentary therapy for mental, emotional, and physical conditions on the planet.</p> <p>And when it comes to ADHD, it’s effectiveness is no different.</p> <p>Meditations can help with things such as reducing fidgeting and improving focus.</p> <p>In <i>Meditations for ADHD</i>, you’ll experience:</p> <ul> <li>Relaxing and effective meditations, written and delivered by pros</li> <li>A guided warm-up proven to calm your mind instantly</li> <li>Narration and prompts specifically designed to trigger critical mental and emotional responses for reducing agitation and impulsiveness</li> <li>Custom guided imagery exercises to remedy six different ADHD symptoms</li> <li>Convenient visualizations that get results but don't take much time to do</li> <li>Powerful affirmations to subconsciously reprogram your mind and body for a more conscious and less hyperactive lifestyle</li> <li>And much more!</li> </ul> <p>Science and medicine are on the side of meditation. But even if you’re still skeptical, what do you have to lose?</p> <p><b>If you want to discover your self-healing power, scroll up, and listen to this audiobook.</b></p>"; 
